OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781002969
OL,3,CLondon robotaxis could be available to
OL,4,Chire 'within months'
OL,6,FITV News Science Correspondent Martin
OL,7,FStew takes a ride in one of the
OL,8,Fdriverless taxis that could be hitting
OL,9,Fthe streets of London within months
OL,11,FSitting in the back of an Uber in
OL,12,FLondon traffic may soon look very
OL,13,Fdifferent.
OL,15,FOn a test journey through the capital,
OL,16,Fthe driver behind the wheel was there
OL,17,Fonly as a safety operator.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781002969
OL,3,CLondon robotaxis could be available to
OL,4,Chire 'within months'
OL,6,FThe steering wheel and pedals moved on
OL,7,Ftheir own as the vehicle navigated the
OL,8,Froads using cameras, artificial
OL,9,Fintelligence and onboard computers.
OL,11,FThe autonomous taxis, known as
OL,12,Frobotaxis, have been operating in
OL,13,Fcities around the world for several
OL,14,Fyears. But bringing the technology to
OL,15,FLondon presents a bigger challenge.
OL,17,FThe capital's narrow streets, many
OL,18,Fdating back to medieval times, are
OL,19,Falso far busier than cities where
OL,20,Frobotaxis already operate.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781002969
OL,3,CLondon robotaxis could be available to
OL,4,Chire 'within months'
OL,6,FLondon has around 20 times more
OL,7,Froadworks and ten times more
OL,8,Fpedestrians and cyclists than San
OL,9,FFrancisco.
OL,11,FUber has partnered with UK technology
OL,12,Fcompany Wayve in a bid to overcome
OL,13,Fthose challenges.
OL,15,FUnlike rival systems which rely
OL,16,Fheavily on GPS, maps and LIDAR (light
OL,17,Fdetection and ranging), Wayve says its
OL,18,Ftechnology uses what it calls
OL,19,F"Autonomy 2.0".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781002969
OL,3,CLondon robotaxis could be available to
OL,4,Chire 'within months'
OL,6,F"Wayve is trained on millions of hours
OL,7,Fof human driving data so just like
OL,8,Fhumans learn to drive we learn the
OL,9,Fsame way," Victor Charoonsophonsak
OL,10,Fexplained.
OL,12,F"We've got surrounding cameras all
OL,13,Fover the whole vehicle which are
OL,14,Fsensing the whole world and
OL,15,Fenvironment."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@JO]tD@AOUwD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
